c1\u09b2\u09a8\u09be \u09b6\u09bf\u09aa\u0987\u09af\u09bc\u09be\u09b0\u09cd\u09a1\u09c7 \u09ac\u09be\u0982\u09b2\u09be\u09a6\u09c7\u09b6 \u0995\u09cb\u09b8\u09cd\u099f \u0997\u09be\u09b0\u09cd\u09a1\u09c7\u09b0 \u09e9\u099f\u09bf \u0987\u09a8\u09b6\u09cb\u09b0 \u09aa\u09c7\u099f\u09cd\u09b0\u09cb\u09b2 \u09ad\u09c7\u09b8\u09c7\u09b2-\u098f\u09b0 \u0986\u09a8\u09c1\u09b7\u09cd\u09a0\u09be\u09a8\u09bf\u0995 \u0989\u09a6\u09cd\u09ac\u09cb\u09a7\u09a8 |website=The Daily Inqilab| date=20 June 2019| accessdate=17 October 2019|}}</ref>  They are awaiting commissioning now.\n|-\n| || || Inshore Patrol Vessel || [[CGS Apurbo Bangla]] (P 207) <br />[[CGS Joy Bangla]] (P 20X) || {{BAN}} || {{align|center|315}} || Construction undergoing at [[Dockyard and Engineering Works Limited]]. Apurbo Bangla launched on 3 September 2019.\n|}\n\n==Fast patrol boats==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! style=\"color:#fff; background:#079; width:15%;\"|Class\n! style=\"color:#fff; background:#079; width:10%;\"|Picture\n! style=\"color:#fff; background:#079; width:12%;\"|Type\n! style=\"color:#fff; background:#079; width:17%;\"|Ships\n! style=\"color:#fff; background:#079; width:12%;\"|Origin\n! style=\"color:#fff; background:#079; width:6%;\"|Displacement (Tons)\n! style=\"color:#fff; background:#079; width:28%;\"|Note\n|-\n! colspan=\"7\" style=\"background: lavender;\"| Active (2)\n|-\n|Porte Grande Class |||| [[Patrol boat#Classification|Inshore Patrol Vessel]] || CGS Shet Gang (P 101) <br> CGS Porte Grande (P 102)|| {{BAN}} ||  ||Built at [[Ananda Shipyard and Shipways]], [[Narayanganj]].\n|-\n! colspan=\"7\" style=\"background: lavender;\"| On order (2)\n|-\n|||[[File:Bangladesh Coast Guard patrol craft CGS Shonadia. (26618007659).jpg|200px]]|| Fast [[Patrol Boat]] || [[CGS Kutubdia]] (P 103)<br />[[CGS Sonadia]] (P 104) || {{BAN}} || {{align|center|235}} || These ships are of 43.4m length, 6.4m breadth and 1.9m draught. They have a displacement of 235 tons, maximum speed of 25 knots and maximum range of 1500 Nautical miles. They are able to carry up to 33 personnel. Handed over to the Bangladesh Coast Guard on 1 August 2018.<ref name=\"dewpv\"/> They are awaiting commissioning now.\n|}\n\n==Coastal patrol vessels==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! style=\"color:#fff; background:#079; width:15%;\"|Class\n! style=\"color:#fff; background:#079; width:10%;\"|Picture\n! style=\"color:#fff; background:#079; width:12%;\"|Type\n! style=\"color:#fff; background:#079; width:17%;\"|Ships\n! style=\"color:#fff; background:#079; width:12%;\"|Origin\n! style=\"color:#fff; background:#079; width:6%;\"|Displacement (Tons)\n! style=\"color:#fff; background:#079; width:28%;\"|Note\n|-\n! colspan=\"7\" style=\"background: lavender;\"| Active (4)\n|-\n|[[Type 062 gunboat|Shanghai II]]||[[File:Type 062-class gunboat, October 2014-1.jpg|200px]]|| Coastal Patrol Vessel || CGS Tawfique (P 611) <br> CGS Tawheed (P 612) <br> CGS Tamjeed (P 613) <br> CGS Tanveer (P 614)|| {{CHN}} || {{align|center|135}} || Transferred from [[Bangladesh Navy]].\n|}\n\n==Riverine patrol craft==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! style=\"color:#fff; background:#079; width:15%;\"|Class\n! style=\"color:#fff; background:#079; width:10%;\"|Picture\n! style=\"color:#fff; background:#079; width:12%;\"|Type\n! style=\"color:#fff; background:#079; width:17%;\"|Ships\n! style=\"color:#fff; background:#079; width:12%;\"|Origin\n! style=\"color:#fff; background:#079; width:6%;\"|Displacement (Tons)\n! style=\"color:#fff; background:#079; width:28%;\"|Note\n|-\n! colspan=\"7\" style=\"background: lavender;\"| Active (5)\n|-\n|[[Pabna Class]]|||| Riverine Patrol Craft || [[CGS Pabna]] (P 111) <br> [[CGS Noakhali]] (P 112) <br> [[CGS Patuakhali]] (P 113) <br> [[CGS Rangamati]] (P 114) <br> [[CGS Bogra]] (P 115)|| {{BAN}} || 75 || Transferred from [[Bangladesh Navy]].\n|}\n\n==Harbour patrol boats==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! style=\"color:#fff; background:#079; width:15%;\"|Class\n! style=\"color:#fff; backgrou